## Background

I learned a lot while doing these plots. First I think I learned how much work is going to be required in future case studies. Second I learned a lot about ggplot and how it works. I have always wanted to learn ggplot, but never really had the exposure. I learned how to plot lines and dots and manipulate them into a form that best represents the data. 

## Data Wrangling

```{r tidy_data}
# Use this R-Chunk to clean & wrangle your data!

wagap <- gapminder %>%
     group_by(continent, year) %>%
     summarise(mgdp = weighted.mean(gdpPercap, pop),
                mpop = sum(pop/100000))


```




## Data Visualization


```{r plot_data}

ggplot(data = gapminder, mapping = aes(x = lifeExp, y = gdpPercap, size = pop/100000, color = continent)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ year, nrow = 1) +
  scale_y_continuous(,trans = "sqrt", limits = c(0,50000)) 



ggplot( data = gapminder, aes( x = year, y = gdpPercap)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = continent)) + 
  geom_line(aes( color = continent, group = country)) +
  geom_point(data = wagap, mapping = aes( x = year, y = mgdp, size = mpop)) +
  geom_line(data = wagap, mapping = aes( x = year, y = mgdp)) +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = "sqrt", limits = c(0,50000)) +
  facet_wrap( ~ continent, nrow = 1) +
   labs(x = "Year", y = "GDP per capita", size = "Population (100k)") 
theme_bw


```

